03:20.466 --> 03:24.854
I hear there's a lot
of dead bodies and zero leads.

03:24.954 --> 03:26.856
We're still processing
the crime scene.

03:26.956 --> 03:29.225
When we have that information,
I'll let you know.

03:29.325 --> 03:32.295
How many victims? Do you have any leads?

03:32.395 --> 03:34.564
Slow down, slow down.

03:34.664 --> 03:36.904
We're getting reports that
there are multiple survivors.

03:36.899 --> 03:40.303
Can you confirm that?

03:40.403 --> 03:42.705
We'll be releasing
those details when we're ready.

03:42.805 --> 03:46.776
Is it true you discovered cameras
at the scene of the crime?

03:46.876 --> 03:48.716
As soon as we have answers,
I'll let you know.

03:48.711 --> 03:50.280
Next question.

03:54.284 --> 03:56.252
...can you explain that?

03:56.352 --> 03:57.554
As you know,

03:57.654 --> 03:59.455
from the record
of this department,

03:59.555 --> 04:01.524
we will not stop
until justice is served.

04:01.624 --> 04:04.194
That's all
we have time for.

04:04.294 --> 04:08.198
We'll release more information later.

04:08.298 --> 04:10.466
When we know more,
you'll know more. Thank you.

04:10.566 --> 04:12.635
That's all for now,
folks, thanks for coming.

04:12.735 --> 04:16.738
There'll be another press conference later.
Thank you very much.

04:16.839 --> 04:19.909
I wanna watch these videos.
What have we got on those bodies?

04:20.009 --> 04:22.729
- Explosion corrupted half the forensics.
- Okay, what about I.D.'S?

04:22.445 --> 04:24.681
Can't tell if the ones we do
have are male or female.

04:24.781 --> 04:26.632
- Well, figure it out.
- Yes, ma'am.

04:29.869 --> 04:31.069
Jesus.

04:32.455 --> 04:35.992
- Go home, Reese. You're on leave.
- I want on the case.

04:36.092 --> 04:38.728
I have enough on my plate.
I can't deal with your baggage.

04:38.828 --> 04:40.630
Baggage. Is that
what you're calling it?

04:40.730 --> 04:42.465
- I can help.
- We're doing fine.

04:42.565 --> 04:44.634
- Yeah, 'cause Gabe called--
- you're not ready.

04:44.734 --> 04:45.935
I spent three years
in the v.U.

04:46.035 --> 04:47.670
I practically
wrote the manual.

04:47.770 --> 04:50.306
You're not ready.

04:50.406 --> 04:53.458
You need me.
You know what I can do.

04:59.065 --> 05:00.465
Alex...

05:01.984 --> 05:04.369
I need this.

05:12.779 --> 05:14.564
Cavalry's arrived.

05:14.664 --> 05:16.733
What's the eta
on the capture?

05:16.833 --> 05:19.836
Reese, thought I was gonna
have to do this one on my own.

05:19.936 --> 05:22.438
I got your back.
Where we at with the video?

05:22.538 --> 05:24.007
Capture complete
in five minutes.

05:24.107 --> 05:26.376
- How many hours are there?
- About three.

05:26.476 --> 05:27.910
Formats?

05:28.010 --> 05:29.445
Four cameras,

05:29.545 --> 05:31.314
but the fire damage
is glitching the video.

05:31.414 --> 05:32.882
I think it's
slowing down the capture.

05:32.982 --> 05:34.884
Next time, copy it
to the hard drive

05:34.984 --> 05:36.719
before the server,
it's faster.

05:36.819 --> 05:38.488
Right. Yeah. Yes, sir.

05:38.588 --> 05:40.523
Update on
our survivor?

05:40.623 --> 05:42.959
Still unresponsive.
Third-degree burns,

05:43.059 --> 05:45.859
massive lacerations to the head and neck.
I got a uniform standing by.

05:45.895 --> 05:48.335
- The other one still with psych?
- There were two survivors.

05:48.064 --> 05:50.224
Looking for some answers,
but it's gonna take a while.

05:50.099 --> 05:52.669
Testimony after trauma
like this is useless anyway.

05:52.769 --> 05:56.906
Witnesses lie,
the camera doesn't.

05:57.006 --> 05:58.941
Capture's complete.
Popcorn's hot.

05:59.041 --> 06:01.611
- Let's hope they caught something.
- They better have.

06:01.711 --> 06:03.546
We got a pile of
dead bodies out there.

06:03.646 --> 06:06.049
These videos could be
the best evidence we've got.

06:06.149 --> 06:08.367
Okay. Do it.

06:29.672 --> 06:31.974
...is the man that holds
the power of God.

06:32.074 --> 06:35.026
That is true greatness.

06:38.097 --> 06:40.583
Oh, that wasn't
good, was it?

06:43.152 --> 06:44.687
Is it too much?

06:44.787 --> 06:47.390
I can't tell.
I'm a terrible actor.

06:47.490 --> 06:49.525
Leann, if I was watching it,
I'd eat it up, so...

06:49.625 --> 06:51.625
- Really?
- Literally. I would totally believe it.

06:51.494 --> 06:52.695
Good. Then we got it.

06:52.795 --> 06:54.497
You promised me
at least--

06:54.597 --> 06:56.833
no, no, leann.
You said at least five.

06:56.933 --> 06:59.068
You said...
All right, all right.

06:59.168 --> 07:00.768
Hold on.

07:03.806 --> 07:06.576
It's beautiful.
What are you playing there?

07:06.676 --> 07:08.544
What's it called?

07:08.644 --> 07:11.663
- It's called--
- shit! Put it down!

07:23.593 --> 07:25.393
Surprise!

07:26.596 --> 07:28.796
Oh, my God!

07:30.032 --> 07:32.001
I can't believe
you got the part.

07:32.101 --> 07:33.870
Oh, my God!

07:33.970 --> 07:36.005
You're a shining star.

07:36.105 --> 07:37.974
- Surprise!
- Surprise!

07:38.074 --> 07:41.077
A little late,
but better late than never, right?

07:41.177 --> 07:43.513
Did you do this?

07:43.613 --> 07:45.982
Yeah. All single-handedly,
I might add.

07:46.082 --> 07:47.784
Oh, really?

07:47.884 --> 07:50.936
Oh, my God,
this is amazing, you guys.

08:02.648 --> 08:04.834
Leann, you look
beautiful.

08:04.934 --> 08:08.137
Such a nice light.

08:08.237 --> 08:10.222
It's perfect.

08:11.858 --> 08:13.776
What are you
thinking about?

08:13.876 --> 08:14.676
Huh?

08:15.978 --> 08:20.082
That just two years ago,

08:20.182 --> 08:22.218
I was back home
in Kansas,

08:22.318 --> 08:25.521
working at my dad's
flower shop.

08:25.621 --> 08:28.124
I remember dreaming
of this moment.

08:28.224 --> 08:30.059
Being up on the stage

08:30.159 --> 08:32.195
was all I ever
thought about.

08:32.294 --> 08:35.063
All those acting classes...

08:35.164 --> 08:37.232
Then you
met me.

08:37.332 --> 08:39.034
Now look at us.

08:39.135 --> 08:41.537
I mean, you're filming
this documentary,

08:41.636 --> 08:45.541
and if this play
goes well, this could be it.

08:45.641 --> 08:48.911
What's the matter
then?

08:49.011 --> 08:51.247
- Leann?
- Hmm?

08:51.347 --> 08:55.051
- Give me that.
- No, no, no.

08:55.151 --> 08:57.253
Last time,
you nearly broke it.

08:57.353 --> 09:00.022
Okay, fine. Hi.

09:00.122 --> 09:01.991
- Hi, Rachel.
- Hello, everyone.

09:02.091 --> 09:03.693
Oh, is little
director shy?

09:03.793 --> 09:05.761
- A little bit.
- Oh, but you're so cute.

09:05.861 --> 09:08.965
You're so annoying.
Nobody wants to see me.

09:09.065 --> 09:10.933
Oh, wow!
Don't get that close.

09:11.033 --> 09:13.202
I see something
on your head.

09:13.302 --> 09:15.771
There's all kinds of
disasters happening here.

09:15.871 --> 09:17.673
Please let me just
film you again,

09:17.773 --> 09:19.675
because you're what
everybody cares about.

09:19.775 --> 09:21.677
No, but you're
so frickin' cute.

09:21.777 --> 09:23.713
Compromise. We'll both
get in there, okay?

09:23.813 --> 09:26.115
At least
you're in it.

09:26.215 --> 09:28.718
Even though I look like a
goddamn goblin next to you.

09:28.818 --> 09:31.120
Okay, so, America,

09:31.220 --> 09:33.556
are you ready...
Oh, God.

09:33.656 --> 09:35.291
For the story of
leann hookplat...

09:35.391 --> 09:37.693
From the girl
next door...

09:37.793 --> 09:41.046
To America's...

09:47.353 --> 09:49.305
Okay,
what's the deal?

09:49.405 --> 09:52.808
The fire corrupted
a lot of the video.

09:52.908 --> 09:56.746
Okay, fast-forward it to the truck yard.
That's all that matters.

09:56.846 --> 09:58.981
No, no, no.

09:59.081 --> 10:01.841
- We need to see the details, the relationships.
- It's not relevant.

10:01.183 --> 10:04.202
- It doesn't matter.
- Everything on this tape matters.

10:07.873 --> 10:09.859
You heard him.

10:09.959 --> 10:11.176
All right.

10:15.781 --> 10:20.236
The truth had cut me like
the grim reaper's blade itself.

10:20.336 --> 10:22.905
Any man who wields
the power of life and death

10:23.005 --> 10:25.608
is a man that holds
the power of God.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.910
That is true greatness.

10:28.010 --> 10:30.580
And though life
may be short,

10:30.680 --> 10:32.582
and death sudden,

10:32.682 --> 10:35.166
true greatness
lasts forever.

10:45.011 --> 10:48.097
Oh, my God! There's
my little superstar.

10:48.197 --> 10:50.166
Did you like it, really?

10:50.266 --> 10:52.466
Of course. Look, I've got goosebumps.
I'm proud of you.

10:52.435 --> 10:54.837
Do you think any of
this footage is gonna be good?

10:54.937 --> 10:57.373
Are you kidding?
This is gonna be a priceless documentary.

10:57.473 --> 10:59.742
You're gonna be
really famous.

10:59.842 --> 11:02.278
Rach, you and me are gonna
make a movie together one day.

11:02.378 --> 11:04.814
Just you and I.
It's gonna be a masterpiece.

11:04.914 --> 11:07.434
Get back out there. Take another bow.

11:06.949 --> 11:10.086
- You gonna film it?
- Of course. Don't be stupid.

11:24.684 --> 11:24.884
♪

11:36.962 --> 11:43.762
♪ and I just wanna
take you away ♪

11:44.520 --> 11:49.920
♪ can't wait
one more day ♪

11:51.026 --> 11:54.430
♪ be your lover,
be your friend ♪

11:54.530 --> 11:57.833
♪ be your everything
till the end ♪

11:57.933 --> 12:03.855
♪ just let me
take you away ♪

12:10.930 --> 12:12.748
Will you make me

12:12.848 --> 12:15.751
the happiest
musician in L.A.?

12:15.851 --> 12:18.921
Say yes!

12:19.021 --> 12:21.023
What are you doing?

12:21.123 --> 12:23.059
I'm asking you
to marry me.

12:23.159 --> 12:25.995
- What?
- Leann.

12:26.095 --> 12:28.330
No, I can't.

12:33.953 --> 12:37.822
- Tyler, I'm... Ty...
- No, I'm fine.

12:45.931 --> 12:48.784
Just talk to him,
I guess.

12:48.884 --> 12:52.470
I'll make sure
that it gets to him, okay?

12:55.908 --> 12:57.908
Hi, Tyler.

12:58.527 --> 13:01.363
I tried to call you,

13:01.463 --> 13:03.099
and Rachel said
you would watch this,

13:03.199 --> 13:06.168
so... I'm sorry.

13:06.268 --> 13:08.137
You just,
you caught me off-guard,

13:08.237 --> 13:10.372
and I panicked.

13:10.472 --> 13:11.272
I...

13:12.842 --> 13:17.012
I didn't know
what else to do.

13:17.112 --> 13:18.814
Um... hi.

13:18.914 --> 13:20.816
I really think that
you should come,

13:20.916 --> 13:23.152
and I simply can't
take no for an answer.

13:23.252 --> 13:25.421
This is supposed to be
our big celebration.

13:25.521 --> 13:29.291
I think it would be a real
shame to waste these tickets.

13:29.391 --> 13:31.927
Um... I don't know.

13:32.027 --> 13:36.165
I think we've got the room,
we've got the bus.

13:36.265 --> 13:39.902
It'll all be
really fun.

13:40.002 --> 13:42.471
I think you'll forget
about it in an instant,

13:42.571 --> 13:45.141
and I know
she's really sorry.

13:45.241 --> 13:46.208
She's been
really boring.

13:46.308 --> 13:48.344
Um, please come.

13:48.444 --> 13:52.181
I promise I'll be more tolerant of your singing,

13:52.281 --> 13:55.166
which I find
really hard, but okay.

13:57.503 --> 13:59.303
Um, look,

14:01.090 --> 14:03.225
I know you probably
hate me,

14:03.325 --> 14:05.194
and I don't blame you,

14:05.294 --> 14:07.797
but this trip just
won't work without you.

14:07.897 --> 14:10.065
Please come.

14:10.165 --> 14:11.565
Just...

14:12.301 --> 14:15.838
I'm not ready
for marriage right now,

14:15.938 --> 14:19.208
but maybe I will be...
One day.

14:19.308 --> 14:21.993
I still love you.

14:25.164 --> 14:26.515
You gonna film this?

14:26.615 --> 14:29.018
Yeah, I've gotta
film everything.

14:29.118 --> 14:30.853
That was
the deal, remember?

14:30.953 --> 14:32.855
But if he doesn't come,
I look like a loser.

14:32.955 --> 14:35.195
Leann, that's the whole point
of documentary filmmaking.

14:35.224 --> 14:37.259
You've gotta get everything.
We had a deal.

14:37.359 --> 14:39.595
I guess he still has time to make it,
do you think?

14:39.695 --> 14:41.096
Not as much time
as you'd think.

14:41.196 --> 14:43.399
Oh, he looks
friendly, doesn't he?

14:43.499 --> 14:45.334
Yeah.

14:45.434 --> 14:47.469
Do you know
what time it is?

14:47.569 --> 14:50.139
Here's the luxury vehicle we've been supplied.

14:50.239 --> 14:52.608
- Oh, hello.
- Travel in style.

14:52.708 --> 14:55.077
Is there gonna be
a problem?

14:55.177 --> 14:57.246
It's a camera,
not a gun.

14:57.346 --> 15:00.282
I'm gonna grab these.
We gotta get on. Running late.

15:00.382 --> 15:03.352
- Tyler's here.
- Ooh, is that him?

15:03.452 --> 15:05.052
Perfect.

15:09.541 --> 15:12.543
Mmm, he looks
jolly.

15:15.581 --> 15:17.466
Fantastic.

15:17.566 --> 15:20.536
Oh, he brought
his guitar. Great.

15:20.636 --> 15:24.188
Well, viva Las Vegas,
everybody.

15:25.424 --> 15:28.477
Hi, Tyler.
Oh, charming.

15:28.577 --> 15:32.030
Here is the happy,
happy couple.

15:35.367 --> 15:37.486
Does she have
to be here?

15:37.586 --> 15:39.355
Can you turn
that thing off?

15:39.455 --> 15:41.290
Hi. I don't know
if we've met before,

15:41.390 --> 15:43.025
but I'm Rachel.
And I like to film things.

15:43.125 --> 15:46.462
Incredibly uncomfortable
things, so, no.

15:46.562 --> 15:49.632
I said I was sorry,
all right?

15:49.732 --> 15:52.935
I showed up,
didn't I?

15:53.035 --> 15:56.405
Yeah, but can't we just go
back to the way things were.

15:56.505 --> 15:57.905
Please.

16:02.995 --> 16:05.347
Huh. All right,
well, I guess

16:05.447 --> 16:09.018
I'll just cut this part out then.
That's fine.

16:09.118 --> 16:11.020
You can't fix this
with editing.

16:11.120 --> 16:13.222
I can fix anything
with editing.

16:13.322 --> 16:15.925
You know what?
Just because he doesn't wanna have fun

16:16.025 --> 16:18.027
doesn't mean that we
can't have fun for him.

16:18.127 --> 16:19.461
Exactly.

16:19.561 --> 16:21.630
- No. No fun ever.
- Ever.

16:21.730 --> 16:24.633
- Ever.
- Ooh, time to meet the cast.

16:26.568 --> 16:28.370
She's cute.

16:28.470 --> 16:30.239
First stop.

16:38.097 --> 16:41.317
- What are you doing?
- I'm filming.

16:41.417 --> 16:43.052
Vicki, where are you
from originally?

16:43.152 --> 16:44.520
From Russia.

16:44.620 --> 16:46.388
- What brings you here?
- I'm dancing.

16:46.488 --> 16:48.457
Cool. You look
like a dancer.

16:48.557 --> 16:50.192
I love your camera.

16:50.292 --> 16:52.127
My son, he would like
something like this.

16:52.227 --> 16:53.395
Is it heavy?

16:53.495 --> 16:55.680
It's actually
not that heavy.

16:58.550 --> 17:02.004
Hello. It's actually got
really good quality picture,

17:02.104 --> 17:04.239
so it's worth
the weight.

17:04.339 --> 17:05.708
I'll take it back.

17:05.808 --> 17:07.710
He skateboards.

17:07.810 --> 17:11.213
Him and his friends
always take pictures and stuff.

17:11.313 --> 17:13.715
So what's this for again?

17:13.816 --> 17:17.419
Um, it's for my friend back there, leann,

17:17.519 --> 17:19.253
who is gonna be a ultra-famous movie star,

17:19.354 --> 17:21.357
and it's kinda like
one of those

17:21.457 --> 17:23.459
"before they were famous"
type shows.

17:23.559 --> 17:25.527
Do you have that
in Russia?

17:25.627 --> 17:27.762
- Before they were stars?
- I love the show, yeah.

17:27.863 --> 17:31.133
Yeah. We're
all fans.

17:31.233 --> 17:34.003
Including you,
Tyler.

17:34.103 --> 17:37.439
So Vicki, tell us more about this
show you're auditioning for.

17:37.539 --> 17:39.508
It's the new cirque
extravaganza.

17:39.608 --> 17:42.077
Oh, wow, you must be
so thrilled.

17:42.177 --> 17:44.580
I'm a pisces,

17:44.680 --> 17:47.149
so this is like
the universe and the stars

17:47.249 --> 17:49.251
are perfectly aligned
to give me the job.

17:49.351 --> 17:50.652
I was born for it.

17:50.752 --> 17:52.621
It's my dream.

17:52.721 --> 17:55.157
That's great.
Very exciting.

17:55.257 --> 17:57.526
Ooh, is that
a present I can see?

17:57.626 --> 17:59.528
Is it your
birthday?

17:59.628 --> 18:00.796
No. It's my son's.

18:00.896 --> 18:03.132
What'd you
get him?

18:03.232 --> 18:05.234
I'm sorry,
it's personal.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.752
Oh, it's okay.

18:09.421 --> 18:11.789
- Should we cut?
- Yeah, all right.

18:26.872 --> 18:29.173
Got another one.

18:33.345 --> 18:35.764
He looks
quite sweet.

18:38.700 --> 18:40.335
- Hi.
- Hey.

18:40.435 --> 18:41.804
- Say hello.
- Hello.

18:41.904 --> 18:43.572
- What's your name?
- Steven.

18:43.672 --> 18:45.674
- Where you from?
- Wait. How old are you?

18:45.774 --> 18:48.477
- Sixteen.
- You can't even work yet.

18:48.577 --> 18:50.813
- What are you gonna do in Vegas?
- Be an apprentice.

18:50.913 --> 18:53.415
Does your mom
even know you're gone?

18:53.515 --> 18:56.318
Do you wanna see
a trick or not?

18:56.418 --> 18:59.288
Yeah, okay.
So we're here with Steven Lee,

18:59.388 --> 19:02.424
or should I call you
the great Stefan?

19:04.459 --> 19:07.629
I can show you guys
the morph and match,

19:07.729 --> 19:09.647
or maybe even
the coin...

19:11.750 --> 19:14.536
God, did you see that?
That was crazy!

19:14.636 --> 19:16.839
Oh, my God, you have to show Tyler.
Tyler, come here.

19:16.939 --> 19:19.541
You should put that on YouTube;
You'd get a million hits.

19:19.641 --> 19:22.201
Seriously, that's amazing.
Will you do it one more time, please?

19:21.710 --> 19:22.710
Okay.

19:24.897 --> 19:26.697
Freeze frame.

19:28.767 --> 19:30.367
Go back.

19:31.220 --> 19:32.837
Stop the tape.

19:36.175 --> 19:37.508
Who's that?

19:39.178 --> 19:40.745
Go back
a few frames.

19:46.318 --> 19:48.537
There's only three women
on the passenger list--

19:48.637 --> 19:52.407
Rachel Brody, Vicki maracova,
and leann hookplat.

19:52.507 --> 19:54.443
She wasn't
supposed to be there.

19:54.543 --> 19:57.962
Advance forward
three frames.

19:59.731 --> 20:03.385
- Capture that frame and advance one more.
- Sure.

20:03.485 --> 20:04.786
Got it.

20:04.886 --> 20:06.470
Capture again
and then overlay.

20:10.776 --> 20:12.776
Zoom 35 %.

20:14.479 --> 20:17.715
- And what's that inside?
- Pan the image.

20:22.888 --> 20:25.374
- Wow.
- That's gotta be 100 grand easy.

20:25.474 --> 20:26.942
We may have found
our motive.

20:27.042 --> 20:29.322
But if he wanted the money,
why not kill her and take it?

20:28.977 --> 20:31.446
Why slaughter
all the others?

20:31.546 --> 20:33.965
Go over to the dog carrier
on the edge of the bag.

20:35.667 --> 20:36.919
That's army issue.

20:37.019 --> 20:38.736
And capture that frame.

20:41.240 --> 20:42.873
"G. Fleishman."

20:45.244 --> 20:47.729
I don't know,
maybe Gina or glenda.

20:47.829 --> 20:50.299
Call fort irwin, have them
run it through their database

20:50.399 --> 20:52.367
of reserved and retired
military personnel

20:52.467 --> 20:54.570
in California
and Nevada.

20:54.670 --> 20:56.238
Let's see
what they've got.

20:56.338 --> 20:58.907
Keep going. I want to see
who this woman is.

20:59.007 --> 21:02.644
That's amazing.
Will you do it one more time, please?

21:22.948 --> 21:24.600
Whoo! All right!

21:26.468 --> 21:27.748
All right,
just a quick thought.

21:27.669 --> 21:29.571
Should it be
taking this long?

21:29.671 --> 21:31.907
I don't know, but I've been
to Vegas 100 times,

21:32.007 --> 21:34.592
and I've never seen
this road before.

21:39.064 --> 21:43.067
I'm gonna go and have a
word with what's-his-face.

21:44.403 --> 21:45.887
Excuse me. Sorry.

21:45.987 --> 21:47.187
Hello.

21:48.090 --> 21:50.292
So, um, much longer?

21:50.392 --> 21:52.294
What's with the camera?

21:52.394 --> 21:54.463
I'm a director.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.598
You been paid
to direct anything?

21:56.698 --> 21:58.267
No, not yet, but...

21:58.367 --> 22:00.669
So you're a girl
with a camera.

22:00.769 --> 22:03.538
Right. Can I ask why
we're going this way,

22:03.638 --> 22:05.540
because it's not
actually a road out there.

22:05.640 --> 22:07.876
That's a dirt track,
by the looks of it.

22:07.976 --> 22:10.412
I have another pick-up
past kidwell.

22:10.512 --> 22:11.813
This is the only way in.

22:11.913 --> 22:14.583
Stop your damn
complaining!

22:14.683 --> 22:16.685
Excuse me. I was
only asking.

22:16.785 --> 22:18.954
Get that damn thing
out of my face.

22:19.054 --> 22:20.455
What? Sit down.

22:20.555 --> 22:22.557
Out of my face!

22:22.657 --> 22:26.561
Oh, my God!
You fucking psychopath!

22:26.661 --> 22:29.031
- Jesus Christ.
- You all right?

22:29.131 --> 22:30.766
Are you okay?

23:02.063 --> 23:03.632
Out, out, out.

23:03.732 --> 23:06.884
Get out of
the mini-van.

23:28.440 --> 23:30.360
Get away from the bus,
it might explode.

23:30.225 --> 23:32.561
It could be
dangerous.

23:32.661 --> 23:36.131
What were you
expecting out here?

23:36.231 --> 23:37.833
What about the radio?

23:37.933 --> 23:39.835
The radio
was pulled a year ago.

23:39.935 --> 23:41.870
We gotta use
the cell phone.

23:41.970 --> 23:44.106
What do you mean,
they pulled out the radio?

23:44.206 --> 23:46.074
Brilliant.
Brilliant news.

23:46.174 --> 23:48.134
Okay, what are we gonna do?
What are we gonna do?

23:48.210 --> 23:49.810
Fuck me.

23:50.946 --> 23:53.448
What the fuck
is that?

23:53.548 --> 23:56.618
Looks like barbed wire.

23:56.718 --> 23:58.720
It came from
that fence over there.

23:58.820 --> 24:01.089
Oh, my God!
Why didn't you drive around it?

24:01.189 --> 24:02.891
I couldn't see it, could I?

24:02.991 --> 24:04.860
Stop fighting.
This isn't helping anything.

24:04.960 --> 24:07.729
So what are
we gonna do?

24:07.829 --> 24:10.165
We can't go anywhere.
Look at Vicki's leg.

24:10.265 --> 24:13.435
- I'm fine.
- You're not fine. You're bleeding.

24:13.535 --> 24:15.137
There's an emergency phone.

24:15.237 --> 24:18.106
There has to be one
at that truck repair shop.

24:18.206 --> 24:20.008
I didn't see
a truck repair shop.

24:20.108 --> 24:21.710
We just passed it.

24:21.810 --> 24:23.645
Look, I believe him.

24:23.745 --> 24:25.547
If he says there's
a truck repair shop...

24:25.647 --> 24:28.850
I haven't seen anything this entire journey, Tyler.

24:28.950 --> 24:31.153
Let's just try
and walk down there.

24:31.253 --> 24:33.188
I haven't seen another fucking living person.

24:33.288 --> 24:35.690
It's not that far back.
Let's go.

24:35.790 --> 24:37.590
Let's go.

24:37.759 --> 24:39.661
Wait, I'm not leaving
without my son's present.

24:39.761 --> 24:41.161
Vicki, come on,
we don't have time.

24:43.598 --> 24:45.901
It's not safe
in there!

24:46.001 --> 24:47.869
You can't
be serious.

24:47.969 --> 24:50.105
- Vicki!
- It's not worth it.

24:50.205 --> 24:51.706
Get the fuck
out of there!

24:51.806 --> 24:53.775
I'll go.
I'll go.

24:53.875 --> 24:55.710
I don't trust
this guy.

24:55.810 --> 24:57.813
We're not quite
in Vegas yet,

24:57.913 --> 25:00.081
but we'll get there
eventually.

25:00.181 --> 25:02.217
It's a bit of
an adventure.

25:02.317 --> 25:05.086
And there's our
now-destroyed bus,

25:05.186 --> 25:07.889
which is fantastic
news for us.

25:07.989 --> 25:11.389
Okay. Here we go.

25:12.894 --> 25:15.797
I'm thinkin',
what if I died?

25:15.897 --> 25:18.200
I won't ever see
my mom again.

25:18.300 --> 25:21.636
What happened?
Did you run away?

25:21.736 --> 25:24.072
Yeah.
Nick happened.

25:24.172 --> 25:26.372
Who's Nick?

25:26.641 --> 25:29.544
An asshole who was
ruining my life.

25:29.644 --> 25:30.444
Huh.

25:31.580 --> 25:35.150
My mom, she just lets him
do whatever he wants,

25:35.250 --> 25:38.086
and I got pissed
and I just left

25:38.186 --> 25:40.555
without saying
anything.

25:40.655 --> 25:42.858
She's probably worried
sick about you.

25:42.958 --> 25:46.544
Yeah, I need to tell her
I'm sorry.

25:49.314 --> 25:52.016
Leann, leann,
come here for a second.

25:54.052 --> 25:56.705
With everything
that's happening,

25:56.805 --> 25:58.923
does it put everything
into perspective?

26:01.259 --> 26:04.328
Does almost dying kind of put
everything in perspective?

26:09.334 --> 26:11.586
That's right.

26:11.686 --> 26:13.804
We all could've...

26:19.744 --> 26:20.944
Jesus.

26:22.263 --> 26:25.349
Looks like a bomb
hit this place.

26:28.653 --> 26:31.989
As long as they didn't
bomb the damn phone.

26:39.764 --> 26:41.364
Come on.

27:46.665 --> 27:49.033
- How's your leg?
- It's fine.

27:55.306 --> 27:58.008
Are there, like,
faucets or something?

28:03.815 --> 28:05.916
It's all rusted over.

28:09.187 --> 28:12.741
The new favorite
holiday destination

28:12.841 --> 28:15.410
of most people.

28:15.510 --> 28:18.813
Over here we have, um,

28:18.913 --> 28:21.131
dilapidated office.

28:23.034 --> 28:25.869
Crazy broad,
and, um...

28:28.073 --> 28:30.158
Abandoned trucks.

28:30.258 --> 28:31.993
Everything you could want

28:32.093 --> 28:35.479
in a prime holiday
destination. Fantastic.

28:52.230 --> 28:55.116
She was
a figure skater.

28:55.216 --> 28:58.286
Ah. Bet she won gold
in Torino.

28:58.386 --> 29:01.056
We got a phone in
this building back here.

29:01.156 --> 29:03.158
It's gettin' too dark.
Wires are all jumbled up.

29:03.258 --> 29:05.093
Does that thing
have a light on it?

29:05.193 --> 29:07.729
Yeah, it's got a light,
and it's got night vision,

29:07.829 --> 29:09.431
so it'll
be perfect.

29:09.531 --> 29:11.066
That's for her movie.
Use mine.

29:11.166 --> 29:13.101
Are you sure?

29:13.201 --> 29:15.804
I put batteries in this stupid thing three times.

29:15.904 --> 29:18.422
Press "record,"
and the light should come on.

29:19.858 --> 29:21.925
I'm happy someone's
using it.

29:25.396 --> 29:27.182
How you like it, huh?

29:27.282 --> 29:29.384
Not so much fun
like this, is it?

29:29.484 --> 29:32.454
Hm. It's fine.
Just more proof for when I sue you.

29:32.554 --> 29:35.023
Find everybody,
tell 'em to meet here.

29:35.123 --> 29:37.243
I don't wanna be out here
any longer than we have to.

29:37.125 --> 29:38.125
Okay.

29:49.354 --> 29:50.554
Leann.

29:53.792 --> 29:57.245
Leann, Ben's
found a phone, so...

29:57.345 --> 29:59.347
He wants me to
get everyone.

29:59.447 --> 30:01.932
Can you...
Are you in here?

31:31.572 --> 31:34.075
Oh, my God,
what happened?

31:34.175 --> 31:36.211
Where are
you going?

31:36.311 --> 31:38.479
Steven, wait.

31:38.579 --> 31:40.179
Someone!

31:40.648 --> 31:42.584
Anybody, please!

31:42.684 --> 31:44.552
What's going on?

31:44.652 --> 31:47.155
I don't know.
I don't know what happened.

31:50.992 --> 31:52.961
I just found him.

31:57.365 --> 32:00.969
He just came
out of nowhere.

32:01.069 --> 32:04.239
Oh, my God, you guys,
I see somebody.

32:04.339 --> 32:06.374
Oh, my God,
he just ran across.

32:06.474 --> 32:08.977
Everybody inside.
Everybody inside.

32:09.077 --> 32:12.647
Come on,
come on, come on.

32:12.747 --> 32:15.483
First victim,
Steven Lee.

32:15.583 --> 32:17.401
Sixteen years old.

32:19.938 --> 32:23.458
Got him.
It's not her name, it's his.

32:23.558 --> 32:25.260
Gerald fleishman,
retired army sergeant.

32:25.360 --> 32:29.264
Photo lab found
these online.

32:29.364 --> 32:32.066
- That's our girl.
- His wife, Katrina fleishman.

32:32.166 --> 32:34.903
Married for 20 years,
but looks like Gerald had some problems

32:35.003 --> 32:36.471
when he got back
from Iraq.

32:36.571 --> 32:38.673
They called it
post-traumatic stress.

32:38.773 --> 32:40.853
He spent a year at Crescent
park mental institution.

32:40.608 --> 32:42.277
Get this, we just
ran financials.

32:42.377 --> 32:44.946
His entire account
cleaned out two days ago.

32:45.046 --> 32:46.981
Over 90 grand.

32:47.081 --> 32:49.517
Gabe, pull up the mini hd camera
the driver took around back,

32:49.617 --> 32:53.070
- and see if he got any clear shots of it.
- Okay.

32:58.343 --> 32:59.661
How do you like it, huh?

32:59.761 --> 33:02.430
Not so much fun
like this, is it?

33:02.530 --> 33:04.132
Hm, it's fine.

33:04.232 --> 33:06.200
Just more proof
for when I sue you, so...

33:06.300 --> 33:08.202
Find everybody,
tell 'em to meet here.

33:08.302 --> 33:10.422
I don't wanna be out here
any longer than we have to.

33:10.338 --> 33:11.338
Okay.

33:18.629 --> 33:21.131
Step over door.

34:08.045 --> 34:10.246
What have we here?

34:27.482 --> 34:29.681
Goddamn it!

34:47.819 --> 34:49.319
Son of a bitch...

34:57.528 --> 35:01.416
- Is that it?
- Uh, there should be more.

35:01.516 --> 35:03.351
It's still rolling.

35:03.451 --> 35:06.269
We should be
seeing something.

35:08.840 --> 35:11.426
That's not our driver.

35:11.526 --> 35:14.611
- Who is it?
- A better question is when is it?

36:13.471 --> 36:17.725
Geez.

36:40.298 --> 36:42.465
- All right, that's enough.
- Fuck!

36:49.807 --> 36:52.642
I am gonna
nail this bastard.

36:58.950 --> 37:02.786
Um, Gabe, go back
a few frames.

37:07.792 --> 37:10.611
Keep going.
Keep going.

37:10.711 --> 37:12.914
In the reflection.
His face is in the glass.

37:13.014 --> 37:14.749
It's too dark.

37:14.849 --> 37:16.666
Get in closer.

37:21.505 --> 37:23.858
Isolate the sharp
edges of the face.

37:23.958 --> 37:25.875
The wrinkles, the teeth,
the facial hair.

37:30.648 --> 37:33.501
- Okay, what is he doing?
- The shadows will give us a clean outline,

37:33.601 --> 37:35.521
- then we'll invert the color.
- Okay, I got it.

37:35.469 --> 37:36.753
Reverse it again.

37:49.800 --> 37:54.288
- A mask. - That's the welder's
mask we found at the scene.

37:54.388 --> 37:57.625
You work the 91-a.

37:57.725 --> 37:59.860
- What's a 91-a?
- He was a machinist.

37:59.960 --> 38:02.230
Fleishman's unstable,
he has a history of violence,

38:02.330 --> 38:04.465
his wife robs him blind,
he goes mad with revenge.

38:04.565 --> 38:06.701
- Circumstantial.
- Get it out to p.R.

38:06.801 --> 38:08.836
I want his picture on
every news outlet.

38:08.936 --> 38:10.571
We need to keep
checking the video.

38:10.671 --> 38:12.506
You find me some
indisputable evidence,

38:12.606 --> 38:15.243
'cause I'm taking this prick
straight to the chair.

38:15.343 --> 38:17.311
You heard her.

38:17.411 --> 38:20.581
- Let's go.
- Rachel's camera coming up.

38:30.341 --> 38:32.660
Everybody
stay quiet.

38:32.760 --> 38:34.795
Be quiet!

38:34.895 --> 38:36.564
They killed him.

38:36.664 --> 38:38.532
I didn't see anybody
from this end.

38:38.632 --> 38:40.334
You see anything?

38:40.434 --> 38:42.670
Why did they kill Steven?
He was just a kid.

38:42.770 --> 38:45.273
Will you turn
that goddamn camera off?!

38:45.373 --> 38:47.475
The cops will need this
to identify who did this.

38:51.078 --> 38:54.515
They have to know
what happened to us!

38:54.615 --> 38:57.718
What are we gonna do?
What are we gonna do, what are we gonna do?

38:57.818 --> 38:59.587
Maybe we
should run for it.

38:59.687 --> 39:02.957
Run for it?
Have you seen Vicki's leg, Tyler?

39:03.057 --> 39:06.827
We're, like, 40 Miles
away from anything.

39:06.927 --> 39:09.363
And it's
pitch black out there.

39:09.463 --> 39:11.932
We could fall into
a 40-foot ditch,

39:12.032 --> 39:14.792
and never even know it,
not to mention the coyotes, the rattlesnakes.

39:14.735 --> 39:16.671
No, you said there was
an emergency phone.

39:16.771 --> 39:19.507
You said there was an emergency phone.
Can't you fix it?

39:19.607 --> 39:21.876
The wires are split
pretty bad.

39:21.976 --> 39:23.611
Isn't there anything
on the bus,

39:23.711 --> 39:26.080
any wires, tools,
anything you can use?

39:26.180 --> 39:28.015
I might be able
to rig something.

39:28.115 --> 39:30.351
You just said
it was too dangerous.

39:30.451 --> 39:32.851
But if there's something we can use,
he has to go out there.

39:32.753 --> 39:34.889
Take my camera,
use the light.

39:34.989 --> 39:37.058
I might as well put a bull's-eye on my ass.

39:37.158 --> 39:39.327
My camera has night vision.
If I come with you,

39:39.427 --> 39:41.395
we could do that and be totally undetectable.

39:41.495 --> 39:43.998
I'll take your camera.
Give me--

39:44.098 --> 39:46.467
I'm sorry if I was
a prick earlier.

39:46.567 --> 39:48.767
You? Never.

39:48.969 --> 39:51.405
I guess it's my turn
to be a hero now.

39:51.505 --> 39:53.040
They tell me I look
like tom cruise.

39:53.140 --> 39:55.576
Oddly enough,
I can see that.

39:55.676 --> 39:58.579
I saw him, I saw him.
He's on the other side of the yard.

39:58.679 --> 40:00.715
You have to go.

40:00.815 --> 40:02.483
Follow me.

40:02.583 --> 40:04.118
Can you take that?

40:04.218 --> 40:06.403
Go, go, go, quick!

40:56.587 --> 40:57.987
Rachel!

40:58.138 --> 41:00.074
Oh, my God.

41:00.174 --> 41:02.476
Ben. Okay, okay.
Come here.

41:07.665 --> 41:09.650
Okay, just
go straight.

41:09.750 --> 41:12.135
Straight. Just keep going straight.
You're fine.

41:18.826 --> 41:20.728
Oh, my God.
Did you hear that?

41:22.563 --> 41:24.963
Sh. Sh.

41:25.733 --> 41:27.735
The bus should be
right down this hill.

41:27.835 --> 41:30.587
- Okay.
- Let's keep going.

41:34.992 --> 41:37.192
Wait.
Wait.

41:38.178 --> 41:40.714
Is that it?
I can't tell.

41:40.814 --> 41:43.117
Is it just...

41:43.217 --> 41:45.486
That's it,
that's it.

41:45.586 --> 41:47.521
Oh, thank God.

41:47.621 --> 41:49.821
Oh, my God.

41:50.090 --> 41:51.490
Rachel.

42:02.620 --> 42:04.238
I can see
the bus from here.

42:04.338 --> 42:06.574
Ben, Ben,
please.

42:06.674 --> 42:09.692
Please slow down.
You don't know what's out there.

42:30.247 --> 42:33.000
What are you
waiting for? Huh?

42:33.100 --> 42:34.900
I just...

42:44.795 --> 42:46.780
I'm gonna need
some light.

42:46.880 --> 42:48.932
Okay.
I'll figure it out.

42:51.068 --> 42:53.120
Watch yourself.
Are you okay?

42:53.220 --> 42:55.689
Just hurry up, please.

42:55.789 --> 42:58.692
I need to find my tools
so I can pull those speakers.

42:58.792 --> 43:00.227
Careful,
careful.

43:00.327 --> 43:01.527
Wires.

43:02.262 --> 43:04.798
Up here, up here.

43:04.898 --> 43:06.983
- Yeah.
- Hurry.

43:17.027 --> 43:20.147
- Shit.
- What, what?

43:20.247 --> 43:21.982
There was a flare gun.

43:22.082 --> 43:24.051
Why didn't you
say something?

43:24.151 --> 43:25.719
I forgot.

43:25.819 --> 43:27.870
Where is it?

43:31.725 --> 43:34.061
Oh,
my God! Oh, my God!

43:34.161 --> 43:35.696
Who's out there?

43:35.796 --> 43:37.665
Can we please go?
Please, let's just go.

43:37.765 --> 43:40.034
- Wait here.
- Ben, please.

43:40.134 --> 43:42.269
You don't know
who's out there.

43:59.637 --> 44:01.904
You wanna fuck with me?

44:09.897 --> 44:12.015
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

44:24.978 --> 44:28.765
Please, please,
please.

44:46.417 --> 44:48.284
What happened?

44:51.755 --> 44:54.375
- What?
- Ben's dead.

45:05.369 --> 45:07.254
Where's leann?

45:07.354 --> 45:09.056
Her and Tyler--
her and Tyler

45:09.156 --> 45:11.925
leann. Leann!
Where is she?!

45:14.795 --> 45:18.365
Stop that. She went
looking for you.

45:18.465 --> 45:20.665
But they...

45:21.235 --> 45:24.320
They didn't come back.

45:40.037 --> 45:42.972
My son turned ten
last week.

45:45.476 --> 45:49.345
This was supposed to be
his birthday present.

45:51.949 --> 45:54.401
When me and his dad
got divorced,

45:54.501 --> 45:57.920
he had to choose
between us.

45:59.089 --> 46:01.357
He chose his dad.

46:05.195 --> 46:07.915
Yesterday,
I was right there,

46:08.015 --> 46:10.199
at the front
of his house.

46:15.272 --> 46:17.240
And I didn't have...

46:20.344 --> 46:25.766
I didn't have balls
to walk up and give him

46:25.866 --> 46:28.266
his present.

46:29.553 --> 46:31.788
I should tell him...

46:36.560 --> 46:38.795
How sorry I am.

46:40.798 --> 46:43.117
How I love him.

46:43.217 --> 46:46.402
And I'm so damn scared.

46:48.438 --> 46:50.190
What are we
gonna do?

46:50.290 --> 46:51.759
He's here.

46:51.859 --> 46:52.859
What?

46:53.927 --> 46:55.496
He's here.

46:55.596 --> 46:58.381
Get the shot of him.

47:01.318 --> 47:03.318
He's here.

47:50.467 --> 47:53.020
Wait, wait.
No, not yet.

47:53.120 --> 47:55.322
Not yet,
not yet.

47:55.422 --> 47:57.506
Wait.
Okay, now. Now.

48:27.404 --> 48:31.158
Leann, leann.
Oh, my God, oh, my God!

48:37.981 --> 48:41.935
I heard Tyler screaming,
and when I turned around, he was gone.

48:42.035 --> 48:44.435
He was gone.

49:00.470 --> 49:02.422
It's pretty beat up.

49:02.522 --> 49:05.058
I don't know how much
longer it's gonna record for.

49:05.158 --> 49:07.527
Do you really think filming
this matters anymore?

49:07.627 --> 49:10.279
Of course it does.
He has to pay for what he did.

49:11.682 --> 49:14.350
And what he's
going to do.

49:24.261 --> 49:26.546
I know why you're here.

49:26.646 --> 49:28.615
What are
you doing?

49:28.715 --> 49:30.651
Just sayin'
my piece.

